comments.body:
-1. As discussed in https://github.com/apache/arrow/commit/ba2b2ea2301f067cc95306e11546ddb6d402a55c#diff-d5e5df5984ba660e999a7c657039f6af, the way to do this is to pass CMAKE_SHARED_LINKER_FLAGS when invoking CMake

{code}
cmake -DCMAKE_SHARED_LINKER_FLAGS="..." ..
{code}

Another (possibly better) way to produce portable binaries is to use Redhat's devtoolset compiler toolchain. That's how we create portable Linux binaries for Python binary packages
